ai-patthana16.64:0.2_0: Having given the immaculateness of the Dhamma
ai-patthana16.64:0.3_0: Transmigration for the purpose of rightly, etc., that is,
ai-patthana16.64:1.1_0: One thing doesn’t give rise to perceptions of impingement, nor repulsion come to be. The cause of this is another reason.
ai-patthana16.64:1.1_1: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana16.64:3.1_0: Not going for refuge to the impingement, repulsion, views, doubt, conceit, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. ...
ai-patthana16.64:4.1_0: Not seeing the cause, repulsion of impingement, not attracting the flood. ...
ai-patthana16.64:5.1_0: The causes of impingement doesn’t give rise to repulsion. All-Ware there is no cause or condition for the sake of repulsion.
ai-patthana16.64:5.1_1: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana16.64:7.1_0: One who doesn’t give rise to the hindrances, nor gets rid of repulsion. It doesn’t give rise to the hindrances, nor is a cause for the sake of purification.
ai-patthana16.64:7.1_1: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana16.64:9.1_0: Not for the sake of non-existence, nor do they arise for others.
ai-patthana16.64:9.1_1: This is the section in brief.
